# Local Maintainer Context (Example)

Copy this file to `AGENTS.local.md` (which is gitignored).

Purpose:
- Let the agent adapt to your personal workflow without committing private details.

## Maintainer Profile
- Name/handle: <fill in>
- Communication: I may use dictation/speech-to-text. Messages may be long and less structured.
- Preferences:
  - Prefer short, targeted clarification questions when needed.
  - Summarize decisions and next steps after long dictation.
  - Keep public-facing text (issues/PRs/release notes) crisp and non-sloppy.

## Local Machine Paths
- Workspace root(s): <fill in>
- Vintage Story install(s): <fill in>
- Vintage Story data path(s): <fill in>
- Additional profiles: <fill in>

## Testing Setup
- I can run multiple VS installs and multiple logged-in client profiles.
- For changes that affect multiplayer behavior, I can validate with two clients.

## Operational Setup
- Server hosting: Pterodactyl
- Preferred posture:
  - Use a dedicated test server for agentic deploy/restart workflows.
  - Treat prod release actions as high-risk (explicit confirmation for releases).

## Approval Boundaries
- Commits: OK to create local commits on topic branches.
- Push / PR / issue comments / release notes: ask for approval of the exact text/command.
